{{use mdy dates|date=August 2016}}
{{no footnotes|date=August 2017}}
A [[creation myth]] (or creation story) is a cultural, traditional or religious [[myth]] which describes the earliest beginnings of the present world. Creation myths are the most common form of myth, usually developing first in [[oral tradition]]s, and are found throughout human culture. A creation myth is usually regarded by those who subscribe to it as conveying profound [[truth (religious)|truths]], although not necessarily in a [[history|historical]] or literal sense.  They are commonly, although not always, considered ''[[cosmogonical]] myths''—that is they describe the ordering of the [[cosmos]] from a state of [[Chaos (cosmogony)|chaos]] or amorphousness.

